{
  "answer": "> **Original (transliteration):**  \n> Hain aur bhī duniyā meñ sukh̤an-war baḥuṭ acch̤e  \n> Kehte haiñ ke 'Ghalib'-kā hai andaaz̤-e-bayān̤ aur[^1]\n\n> **Translation:**  \n> The world has many poets, it is plain;  \n> But they say Ghalib's mode of speech is something else again.[^2]\n\nThis is the *maqt̤a* (signature couplet) from Ghalib's ghazal \"Hai bas̤k̤e har ek unke is̤hāre meñ niṣ̤ān̤ aur,\" where he acknowledges other fine poets (*sukhanwar*) in the world while claiming his own distinctive style (*andaaz-e-bayaan*).\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/60-hai-baske-har-ek-unke-ishaare-mein-nishaan-aur/transliteration/#p-1f1fad).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/60-hai-baske-har-ek-unke-ishaare-mein-nishaan-aur/translation/#p-312db4).",
